From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jerome Laban <noreply@platform.uno>
Date: Mon, 11 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: emit gsharedvt_out_sig wrappers for cfg->signatures
 alongside gsharedvt_in_sig in LLVMOnly+Interp profile-guided AOT

In LLVMOnly+Interp mode (the WASM worker scenario), the AOT compiler
walks each compiled method's `cfg->signatures` — signatures observed
when emitting indirect calls through rgctx method ftndescs, delegate
Invoke, etc. — and emits only the matching `gsharedvt_in_sig` wrapper
per signature.  The comment said "These only need in wrappers".

That assumption was wrong for the interp→AOT direction.  When a generic
method instantiation is reachable only from the interpreter side
(because the only AOT-compiled method that mentions the signature does
so as an indirect-call sig rather than as its own `cfg->method`
signature), no AOT-compiled method matches the gsharedvt-form of that
signature, so the corresponding `gsharedvt_out_sig` wrapper at line
9742 never gets emitted.

At runtime, when the interpreter has to call an AOT'd method with that
signature, `init_jit_call_info` (`mono/mini/interp/interp.c:2735`)
calls `mini_get_gsharedvt_out_sig_wrapper(sig)`, then
`mono_jit_compile_method_jit_only` on the wrapper.  Because the wrapper
isn't in any AOT image and we are in aot-only mode, the compile fails
with "Attempting to JIT compile method ... while running in aot-only
mode" and the runtime asserts.

Symmetric emission — both `gsharedvt_in` and `gsharedvt_out` — for
`cfg->signatures` closes the gap with a single extra wrapper per
signature.  Build-size impact is bounded by the existing `cfg->signatures`
walk; the wrappers themselves are very small (sig-keyed marshaling IL).

Concrete repro from the Roslyn worker (Roslyn-hosting,
profile-guided AOT, .NET 10):

  [MONO] * Assertion at .../mono/mini/interp/interp.c:2737,
  condition `is_ok (error)' not met, function: init_jit_call_info,
  Attempting to JIT compile method
    '(wrapper other) void object:gsharedvt_out_sig
      (intptr, Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.CompoundUseSiteInfo`1<object>&,
       object&, object&, intptr)'
  while running in aot-only mode.

`llvm-nm` on the AOT'd worker wasm confirms the asymmetry: 11,011
`gsharedvt_out_sig` wrappers total, 8+ `gsharedvt_in_sig` wrappers for
`CompoundUseSiteInfo<object>` signatures, but **zero** `gsharedvt_out_sig`
wrappers for any `CompoundUseSiteInfo<object>` signature.  The 21.7 MB
profile mentions `CompoundUseSiteInfo` 329 times.

---
 src/mono/mono/mini/aot-compiler.c | 27 +++++++++++++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 25 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/mono/mono/mini/aot-compiler.c b/src/mono/mono/mini/aot-compiler.c
index 8e9cdc6120f..a6dd7ec085b 100644
--- a/src/mono/mono/mini/aot-compiler.c
+++ b/src/mono/mono/mini/aot-compiler.c
@@ -9744,8 +9744,31 @@ compile_method (MonoAotCompile *acfg, MonoMethod *method)
 		for (l = cfg->signatures; l; l = l->next) {
 			MonoMethodSignature *sig = mono_metadata_signature_dup ((MonoMethodSignature*)l->data);

-			/* These only need in wrappers */
-			add_gsharedvt_wrappers (acfg, sig, TRUE, FALSE, FALSE);
+			/*
+			 * Emit both gsharedvt_in and gsharedvt_out wrappers for indirect-call
+			 * signatures observed during method compilation.
+			 *
+			 * Historically only gsharedvt_in was emitted here, on the assumption that
+			 * gsharedvt_out coverage from cfg->method's own signature (above) was
+			 * sufficient. That assumption breaks in LLVMOnly+Interp (profile-guided
+			 * AOT) when a generic method instantiation is reached only via the
+			 * interpreter side: the AOT compiler observes the signature in
+			 * cfg->signatures of some other method (indirect call through rgctx
+			 * ftndesc, delegate.Invoke, etc.) but never compiles a method whose
+			 * cfg->method signature matches, so no gsharedvt_out_sig wrapper is
+			 * emitted. The interpreter then asserts in init_jit_call_info
+			 * (interp/interp.c) when calling into the AOT'd target, because
+			 * mono_jit_compile_method_jit_only on the wrapper returns the
+			 * "Attempting to JIT compile method ... while running in aot-only mode"
+			 * error.
+			 *
+			 * Concrete repro using Roslyn (Roslyn-hosting worker, .NET 10):
+			 *   gsharedvt_out_sig (intptr, Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.CompoundUseSiteInfo`1<object>&,
+			 *                      object&, object&, intptr)
+			 * The same signature already gets a gsharedvt_in wrapper from this loop;
+			 * emitting the out wrapper symmetrically closes the gap.
+			 */
+			add_gsharedvt_wrappers (acfg, sig, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE);
 			if (mono_aot_mode_is_interp (&acfg->aot_opts) && sig->param_count > MAX_INTERP_ENTRY_ARGS)
 				/* See below */
 				add_gsharedvt_wrappers (acfg, sig, FALSE, FALSE, TRUE);
--
2.43.0
